# React Component Rules

## Presentational / Container Pattern

- Components in `packages/ui/` are **dumb** (presentational): props in, callbacks out, no side effects.
- Components in `apps/desktop/src/containers/` are **smart**: they connect stores, invoke Tauri commands, and pass data to dumb components.
- Never import Zustand stores, Tauri commands, or API clients inside `packages/ui/`.

## Component Structure

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Dumb component
interface TaskCardProps {
  title: string
  status: TaskStatus
  energyLevel?: EnergyLevel
  onStatusChange: (status: TaskStatus) => void
  onPress: () => void
}

export function TaskCard({ title, status, energyLevel, onStatusChange, onPress }: TaskCardProps) {
  return (/* JSX */)
}
```

## Every UI Component MUST Have

1. **Typed props interface** — exported, named `{Component}Props`
2. **Storybook story** — co-located `{Component}.stories.tsx` with all visual states
3. **Unit test** — co-located `{Component}.test.tsx` testing behavior with React Testing Library
4. **No hardcoded colors/spacing** — use design tokens from `@locus/tokens` via Tailwind classes

## Atomic Design Hierarchy

- `atoms/`: Button, Input, Badge, Chip, Icon, Spinner, Tooltip, ProgressBar
- `molecules/`: SearchBar, FormField, Card, TimerBlock, EmptyState
- `organisms/`: TaskCard, NotePreview, EntityCard, InterventionCard, MeetingCard
- `templates/`: SplitView, ModalLayout, SidebarLayout, CommandCenter

Higher-level components compose lower-level ones. Never skip levels (e.g., a template should not import an atom directly without a molecule or organism in between).

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements have an accessible name (label, aria-label, or aria-labelledby).
- All buttons have `type="button"` unless they submit a form.
- Focus is visually indicated and keyboard-navigable.
- Use semantic HTML elements (`button`, `input`, `nav`, `main`, `section`) over generic `div`.

## Icons

- Use **Lucide React** (`lucide-react`) for all icons. No other icon library.
- Import icons individually for tree-shaking: `import { Search, Plus } from 'lucide-react'`
- Never use raw SVGs for standard UI icons — always check if Lucide has the icon first.
- Pass `size`, `strokeWidth`, and `className` as props for customization.
- Use `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative icons. Use `aria-label` on icon-only buttons.

## Styling & Theming

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes. No inline styles. No CSS modules.
- Responsive design via Tailwind breakpoints.
- Both light and dark themes must work. Use semantic classes (`bg-surface`, `text-primary`), never raw colors.
- Always provide `dark:` variants when using theme-dependent colors.
- Storybook stories must render correctly in both themes.
- Animations use `@locus/tokens` animation values. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Internationalization

- No hardcoded user-facing strings. Use `t('namespace:key')` from `@locus/i18n`.
- Feature-level organisms and templates must include a `HelpButton` with the relevant topic.
- Storybook stories must render correctly in both English and Polish locales.
